791
01:10:00,421 --> 01:10:02,304
[SPEAKER_12]: And I see them in my constituency surgeries.

792
01:10:02,364 --> 01:10:19,046
[SPEAKER_12]: I see people who are desperately trying to fill in the forms to go from disability living allowance to the personal independence payment, and they are absolutely overwhelmed by the bureaucracy and they are also overwhelmed by the fact that there are deliberate targets which actually mean that some of them simply can't get the funding that they deserve.

793
01:10:19,066 --> 01:10:22,731
[SPEAKER_12]: So let no one be under any illusion that this is happening by accident.

794
01:10:22,771 --> 01:10:26,496
[SPEAKER_12]: This is a cruel and callous government, and the sooner it goes, the better.

795
01:10:30,138 --> 01:10:34,407
[SPEAKER_04]: Let's just reset a bit and remind us of Almaz's question.

796
01:10:34,447 --> 01:10:42,022
[SPEAKER_04]: She was talking about how hard life is at the moment, the price of her weekly shopping continues to rise, bills increasing, wages and benefits have hardly gone up.

797
